<div ana="#b1" corresp="#hamm0052.transcription #hamm0052.translation" subtype="diplomatic" type="edition" xml:id="hamm0052.diplomatic">
<p>+ΟΚΑΙCΡΕΥCΤΟΝΟΙΚΟΝ<lb/>
ΑΛΕΞΑΝΔΡΟCΠΟΕΙ<lb/>
ΟΤΗΝΧΛΙΑΡΩΝΕΠΩΝΥΜΟΝ<lb/>
ΘΟΛΟΝ ΚΑΜΩΝ.
</p>
</div>
<div ana="#b1" corresp="#hamm0052.diplomatic #hamm0052.translation" subtype="transcription" type="edition" xml:id="hamm0052.transcription">
<p>
Ὁ Καισαρεὺς τὸν οἶκον <lb/>Ἀλέξανδρος ποεῖ,<lb/>
ὁ τὴν χλιαρῶν ἐπώνυμον <lb/>θόλον καμών. 

		  </p>
</div>
<div ana="#b1" corresp="#hamm0052.diplomatic #hamm0052.transcription" type="translation" xml:id="hamm0052.translation">
<p>
<persName ref="persons.xml#hamm0052p01" xml:lang="grc ">Alexander </persName> of <rs type="ethnicon">Caesarea </rs> is the maker of the building, he who built the tholos of the lukewarm pool that is named after him.</p>
</div>
</body>
